      <Text fill="WHITE" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="     Visible faintly through the glow of a flickering bulb, the room is enveloped in a thin veil of dust. Sprawled across desks and pooling onto the floor are various newspaper articles, letters, and typewriters frozen mid-sentence. " translateX="-120.0" translateY="35.0" wrappingWidth="451.21630859375" GridPane.columnIndex="1" />
      <Text fill="WHITE" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="     Strewn across the newspapers are scathing headlines that do everything to catch your eye. Mayors running speakeasies, covered-up murders of famous musicians." translateX="-120.0" translateY="-20.0" wrappingWidth="440.21630859375" GridPane.columnIndex="1" GridPane.rowIndex="1" />
      <Text fill="WHITE" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="     This was the office of Gordon Parker, a newspaper editor and political whistleblower who vanished after claiming to uncover a government cover-up tied to the citys booming industries. Files, telegrams, coded notes. Time may have erased Gordon Parkers name, but not his truth-if you're willing to search for it." translateX="-120.0" translateY="-75.0" wrappingWidth="452.21630859375" GridPane.columnIndex="1" GridPane.rowIndex="2" />
